vectorData.altText: 21. What organ will epithelium A line? Be specific.
That's right! Transitional epithelium lines surfaces that stretch and recoil, such as urinary bladder and ureter.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.

Transitional epithelium is a stratified epithelium that lines surfaces which must allow stretch & recoil, such as the urinary bladder and ureter
surface cells are domed in shape, when the organ is empty and the epithelium is therefore not under tension.
cells flatten, epithelium appears to consist of fewer layers, as the organ fills and the epithelium must stretch
